channel.topic: All Pilot Ranks and their Operational Ability’s are posted below.

embeds.title: Pilot Rank Structure:
embeds.description:
```Pilot Ranks:```
:ThirdOfficer: @Third Officer 0 - 9
:SecondOfficer: @Second Officer  10 - 69
:FirstOfficer: @First Officer  70 - 199 
:FirstOfficer: @Reserve Captain  200 - 399 
:seniorCaptain: @Line Captain  400 - 649 
:ExecutiveCaptain: @Senior Captain  650 + 

*Members will need to obtain **both** the hours and XP minimums in order to promote to the next rank.*
```Pilot Route Restrictions:```
:ThirdOfficer: @Third Officer: Restricted to FDXV/ TNT /Atlas Air routes.
:SecondOfficer:  @Second Officer : Restricted to FDXV/ TNT /Atlas Air routes.
:FirstOfficer: @First Officer : Restricted to FDXV/ TNT /Atlas Air routes.
:Captain: @Reserve Captain: Unlocks Codeshare routes.
:seniorCaptain: @Line Captain Unlocks Charters.

*Restrictions do not apply to events or special routes like ROTW.* 
```Pilot Rank Bonuses:```
:Captain: @Reserve Captain  1.2X
:seniorCaptain:  @Line Captain  1.3X
:ExecutiveCaptain: @Senior Captain  1.4X

*Captain level rank bonuses may not be combined with any other bonuses unless noted.*
```
Pilot Rank XP Minimums:
```
:ThirdOfficer: @Third Officer - 0xp
:SecondOfficer: @Second Officer - 200xp
:FirstOfficer: @First Officer - 400xp
:Captain: @Reserve Captain - 1,000xp
:seniorCaptain: @Line Captain - 3,500xp
:ExecutiveCaptain: @Senior Captain -20,000xp

*Members will need to obtain **both** the hours and XP minimums in order to promote to the next rank.*
